Experiment 5(e): Deploy a Full Stack Application on a Cloud Platform
Aim
To deploy a Spring Boot web application on cloud platforms like Heroku, AWS Elastic Beanstalk, or GitHub Pages.
Theory
Cloud deployment allows applications to be hosted online for access by users worldwide.


Procedure / Steps

1.	Install Git and Heroku CLI on your system.
2.	Login to Heroku using: heroku login.
3.	Create a new app: heroku create your-app-name.
4.	Add a Procfile specifying how to run the app.
5.	Commit code and push to Heroku using Git.
6.	For AWS: Package JAR and upload using Elastic Beanstalk console.
7.	For static React frontend: Build project and deploy to GitHub Pages.


Source Code / SQL Commands:

web: java -jar target/SpringApp-0.0.1-SNAPSHOT.jar
git add .
git commit -m "deploy"
git push heroku main


Expected Output
Application should be accessible through a public URL hosted on the chosen cloud platform.
Result
Full stack application was successfully deployed to a cloud environment.
